It would be useful to edit the *Blank page* template (the one most used) to be able to add a warn message. For example, a message that reminds users about adding page restrictions when necessary.

h4. Possible workarounds:

This can be achieved by adding one of the following scripts "At end of the HEAD" section of {{Confluence Admin > Custom HTML}}:

* First option:
{code}
<div class="messageBox"
style="display: none;
padding:10px;
border:1px solid #FF0000;
margin-left: 200px;
margin-right: 200px;
z-index:999;
font-weight: bold;
-webkit-border-radius: 6px
-moz-border-radius: 6px;">
Please make use of the page restrictions feature to lock down your page based on the sensitivity of your content. </br>If you don't see that option, ask your space admin or contact Confluence Support.
</div>  
<script type="text/javascript">
if (location.pathname=="/pages/createpage.action" || location.pathname=="/plugins/createcontent/draft-createpage.action" || location.pathname=="/pages/createblogpost.action") {
               AJS.toInit(function() {
                              AJS.$(document).ready(function() {  
                                             AJS.$('.messageBox').show();
                                             setTimeout(function() {  
                                                            AJS.$('.messageBox').fadeOut('fast');  
                                             }, 5000); // <-- time in milliseconds  
                              });  
               });
}
</script>
{code}
This uses a message box that is displayed for the number of milliseconds you set.

* Second option:

{code}
<script type="text/javascript">
  if(location.pathname=="/pages/createpage.action")
  alert('Add your warning here');
</script>
{code}

This uses the [Javascript window alert() method|http://www.w3schools.com/jsref/met_win_alert.asp] to generate the pop-up, which should be supported by all modern browsers. 

(i) Note that if context path in your base URL, e.g. "/wiki" or "/confluence", then the pathname in the script should be modified to reflect this.

(i) Please keep in mind such customizations are not part of our [support offerings|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/Support/Atlassian+Support+Offerings]. The content provided here should be taken as example, and needs to be tested/modified/reviewed accordingly.

